The article celebrates Read Across America Day, emphasizing the importance of reading skills for every American. It highlights the benefits of reading in enriching personal and professional lives, as well as enhancing political discourse. The article stresses the significance of promoting youth literacy and instilling a love of reading at a young age. It calls for a united effort in ensuring that every citizen receives the rewarding gift of learning how to read. The article concludes with a quote from Dr. Seuss, encouraging individuals to believe in their own abilities and make their own choices.